LINE 5:      JOIN t2 FOR KEY (c3) -> q1 (c1);
                     ^
DETAIL:  There is no matching foreign key constraint for t2 (c3) referencing q1 (c1).
SELECT *
FROM t1 AS outer_t,
     LATERAL (SELECT outer_t.c1 WHERE false) AS q1(c1)
-- rejected, reason: LATERAL referenced side can suppress inherited keys
     JOIN t2 FOR KEY (c3) -> q1 (c1);
ERROR:  key join from referencing relation t2 to referenced relation q1 cannot be proven
LINE 5:      JOIN t2 FOR KEY (c3) -> q1 (c1);
                     ^
