SELECT * FROM
(
    SELECT c1, c2 FROM t1 WHERE c2 > 0
) AS u
-- rejected, reason: a filter on the referenced side defeats row coverage
JOIN t2 FOR KEY (c3, c4) -> u (c1, c2);
ERROR:  key join from referencing relation t2 to referenced relation u cannot be proven
LINE 6: JOIN t2 FOR KEY (c3, c4) -> u (c1, c2);
                ^
DETAIL:  Not every t2 (c3, c4) value can be proven to have a matching u row. Referenced relation u is filtered before this key join.
